{"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/TileMap"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/TileMap\/updateInternals()"},"metadata":{"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot7TileMapC15updateInternalsyyF","symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"title":"updateInternals()","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"updateInternals"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Triggers a direct update of the TileMap. Usually, calling this function is not needed, as TileMap node updates automatically when one of its properties or cells is modified."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"updateInternals","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"However, for performance reasons, those updates are batched and delayed to the end of the frame. Calling this function will force the TileMap to update right away instead."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"warning","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Updating the TileMap is computationally expensive and may impact performance. Try to limit the number of updates and how many tiles they impact."}]}],"name":"Warning"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/tilemap\/updateinternals()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentatio